relatedViews.name: NYPD Complaint Map (Year to Date)
relatedViews.description: This dataset includes all valid felony, misdemeanor, and violation crimes reported to the New York City Police Department (NYPD) for all complete quarters so far this year (2016).  Offenses occurring at intersections are represented at the X Coordinate and Y Coordinate of the intersection. Crimes occurring anywhere other than an intersection are geo-located to the middle of the block. For additional details, please see the attached data dictionary in the ‘About’ section.
